    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 17, 2025
    </div>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>Drawing Perfect Shapes（完美图形）</strong> ("we", "us", or "our") developed the 
        <strong>Drawing Perfect Shapes</strong> mobile application (the "App"). 
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our App.
    </p>
    <p>
        By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>Drawing Perfect Shapes collects the following types of data:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Drawing Data</strong>: Shapes and patterns you create within the App</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: 
            <ul>
                <li>Challenge completion progress</li>
                <li>Accuracy scores and star ratings</li>
                <li>Feature interaction patterns</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Device Information</strong> (automatic collection):
            <ul>
                <li>Device model and OS version</li>
                <li>Screen dimensions and orientation</li>
                <li>Language and region settings</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use collected data to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain drawing functionality</li>
        <li>Calculate shape accuracy scores in real-time</li>
        <li>Track user progress across difficulty levels</li>
        <li>Improve algorithm performance for scoring system</li>
        <li>Personalize challenge recommendations</li>
        <li>Analyze crash reports for stability improvements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Storage & Protection</h2>
    <p><strong>Storage Location</strong>: All data is stored locally on your device using iOS Core Data framework.</p>
    <p><strong>Backups</strong>: iCloud backups may include your drawing progress if you enable iCloud Sync in settings.</p>
    <p><strong>Security Measures</strong>: 
        <ul>
            <li>Data encryption at rest using iOS Data Protection API</li>
            <li>Secure authentication for premium content access</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We use these integrated services:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>RevenueCat</strong>: For in-app purchase management (subject to <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" target="_blank">RevenueCat Privacy Policy</a>)</li>
        <li><strong>Crashlytics</strong>: For crash reporting (anonymous device data only)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. User Rights</h2>
    <p>You can:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access your drawing history via <em>Profile > My Gallery</em></li>
        <li>Delete account data in <em>Settings > Reset Progress</em></li>
        <li>Export drawings as PNG files</li>
        <li>Disable iCloud Sync anytime</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App does not knowingly collect data from children under 13. All drawing activities are COPPA-compliant.</p>

    <h2>8. Policy Changes</h2>
    <p>Updates will be posted on this page with revised "Last Updated" date. Continued use constitutes acceptance.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>For privacy inquiries: <br> 
        <strong>Email</strong>: 544736399@qq.com<br>

